
==========================
 * From theorem premises:
A B C D : Points
BD ⟂ AC [00]
CD ⟂ AB [01]

 * Auxiliary Constructions:
E : Points
E,B,D are collinear [02]
E,A,C are collinear [03]

 * Proof steps:
001. E,B,D are collinear [02] & E,A,C are collinear [03] & BD ⟂ AC [00] ⇒  ∠BEA = ∠CED [04]
002. E,B,D are collinear [02] & E,A,C are collinear [03] & BD ⟂ AC [00] ⇒  ∠BEC = ∠AED [05]
003. E,B,D are collinear [02] & E,A,C are collinear [03] & BD ⟂ AC [00] ⇒  EB ⟂ EA [06]
004. EB ⟂ EA [06] & CD ⟂ AB [01] ⇒  ∠(EB-DC) = ∠EAB [07]
005. E,A,C are collinear [03] & E,D,B are collinear [02] & ∠(EB-DC) = ∠EAB [07] ⇒  ∠BAE = ∠CDE [08]
006. ∠BEA = ∠CED [04] & ∠BAE = ∠CDE [08] (Similar Triangles)⇒  EB:EC = EA:ED [09]
007. EB:EC = EA:ED [09] & ∠BEC = ∠AED [05] (Similar Triangles)⇒  ∠BCE = ∠ADE [10]
008. EB:EC = EA:ED [09] & ∠BEC = ∠AED [05] (Similar Triangles)⇒  ∠EBC = ∠EAD [11]
009. ∠BCE = ∠ADE [10] & E,A,C are collinear [03] & E,B,D are collinear [02] & ∠EBC = ∠EAD [11] ⇒  AD ⟂ BC
==========================
